-- IDBI Bank to Start Meeting With Investors in Asia for Dollar Bond Sale
-- Katrina Nicholas
-- 2010-07-26T06:19:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/idbi-bank-to-start-meeting-with-investors-in-asia-for-dollar-bond-sale.html

          
          
             IDBI Bank Ltd., an Indian state-
owned lender, plans to meet with credit investors in Singapore,
Hong Kong and London on July 27, 28 and 29 respectively,
according to a person familiar with the matter.  
 The bank is considering selling dollar bonds to raise about
$500 million, Executive Director Melwyn Rego said in an
interview on July 21.  
          
          


  


        